    <section id="course-description" class="content-section collapsible">
      <h2>Course Description and Objectives</h2>
      <article>
        <h3>ENGLISH C1000 (*course title*)</h3>
        <p>This is an introductory course in rhetoric that emphasizes clear, effective written communication and preparation of the research paper...</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Identify the thesis, major supporting points (both stated and implied), and the logical argument of an essay they have read.</li>
          <li>Analyze intent, style, logic, tone, and rhetorical devices in source materials.</li>
          <li>Synthesize information from multiple sources...</li>
          <!-- truncated for brevity -->
        </ul>
      </article>
      <article>
        <h3>ENGLISH 28 (Intensive College Writing Skills)</h3>
        <p>This course emphasizes clear, effective written communication and preparation of the research paper to prepare students for success...</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Practice the writing process, including pre-writing, planning, drafting, revising and editing.</li>
          <li>Create organizational tools for multi-page essays.</li>
          <!-- truncated for brevity -->
        </ul>
      </article>
    </section>

    <section id="course-requirements" class="content-section collapsible">
      <h2>Course Requirements</h2>
      <p>To successfully complete this course, you will need to have the following:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Course texts: All course texts will be Open Educational Resources posted on Canvas. No textbook required.</li>
        <li>Reliable access to a computer and internet.</li>
        <li>A notebook for notes and essay planning.</li>
        <li>Writing utensils for in-class activities.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>To successfully complete the course, you will need to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Participate weekly in class discussions.</li>
        <li>Complete journals, quizzes, and essays on time.</li>
        <li>Propose, draft, write, and revise 4 essays ranging from 500-2500 words.</li>
        <li>Complete midterm and final exams.</li>
        <li>Understand Canvas and its use.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

